{"key":"processedPost-7903255","value":{"id":7903255,"first":7902193,"last":7903360,"when":1200797888,"utime":"01/20/08 04:58 AM","content":"You don't need to vary the agar recipe.  I've used MEA for 20+ years on all my cultures, and they're fine. Eating the same food doesn't cause senescence, cell divisions do. <br /><br />When working with wild prints, I'll often use antibiotic agar, and mix it with less malt.  If you buy pre-mixed agar powder from fp or sporeworks, you can mix it a bit weaker than recommended.  This will keep from feeding the mold and bacteria quite so much.<br /><br />When you get the video back, watch the section on strain isolation.  It demonstrates the best places to take transfers.<br />RR","title":"Re: considering trying out some agar...please help.","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}